cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with action detection in videos using deep neural networks, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel deep net framework, which involves training the network end-to-end, making it a likely candidate for cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves classification and regression, which are common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed model is tested on action detection datasets, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also involves an algorithm for linking up micro-tubes into complete action tubes, which could be considered as a problem in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
